First rewrite \(x^2-25=(x-5)(x+5)\).  Then the denominator becomes

\[
\frac{3}{x-5}+\frac{1}{(x-5)(x+5)}
=\frac{3(x+5)+1}{(x-5)(x+5)}
=\frac{3x+16}{x^2-25}.
\]

So the whole expression is

\[
\frac{\frac{2}{x+5}}{\frac{3x+16}{x^2-25}}
=\frac{2}{x+5}\cdot\frac{x^2-25}{3x+16}
=\frac{2(x-5)(x+5)}{(x+5)(3x+16)}
=\frac{2(x-5)}{3x+16}\,,
\]

with \(x\neq\pm5\) (and \(3x+16\neq0\), i.e.\ \(x\neq-16/3\)).

First note that  
a² – 2a – 15 = (a – 5)(a + 3).  

So the expression is  

 \frac{4/[(a–5)(a+3)]}{\,1/(a–5)+2/(a+3)\!}  

Combine the terms in the denominator:  
1/(a–5)+2/(a+3)  
= \frac{(a+3)+2(a–5)}{(a–5)(a+3)}  
= \frac{a+3+2a–10}{(a–5)(a+3)}  
= \frac{3a–7}{(a–5)(a+3)}.  

Hence the original becomes  

 \frac{4/[(a–5)(a+3)]}{(3a–7)/[(a–5)(a+3)]}  
= 4 · \frac{(a–5)(a+3)}{(a–5)(a+3)} · \frac{1}{3a–7}  
= \frac{4}{3a–7},  

with the restrictions a ≠ 5, –3, 7/3.

First note that  
c² + 9c + 14 = (c + 2)(c + 7).  

So the given expression is

\[
\frac{\frac{5}{c+2}-\frac{3}{c+7}}{\frac{5c}{(c+2)(c+7)}}
=\Bigl(\frac{5}{c+2}-\frac{3}{c+7}\Bigr)\;\Bigl/\;\frac{5c}{(c+2)(c+7)}
\]

Compute the difference in the numerator:

\[
\frac{5}{c+2}-\frac{3}{c+7}
=\frac{5(c+7)-3(c+2)}{(c+2)(c+7)}
=\frac{5c+35-3c-6}{(c+2)(c+7)}
=\frac{2c+29}{(c+2)(c+7)}.
\]

Hence the whole thing becomes

\[
\frac{2c+29}{(c+2)(c+7)}\;\cdot\;\frac{(c+2)(c+7)}{5c}
=\frac{2c+29}{5c},
\]

with the restrictions \(c\neq -2,\,-7,\,0\).

First write the denominator as a single fraction:

4 + \tfrac1{m-5}
= \frac{4(m-5)}{m-5} \;+\;\frac1{m-5}
= \frac{4m-20+1}{m-5}
= \frac{4m-19}{m-5}.

Hence the original expression is

\[
\frac{\frac{m}{m+5}}{4+\frac1{m-5}}
=\frac{m}{\,m+5\,}\,\Big/\!\frac{4m-19}{m-5}
=\frac{m}{m+5}\cdot\frac{m-5}{4m-19}
=\frac{m\,(m-5)}{(m+5)(4m-19)}.
\]

Domain restrictions: \(m\neq -5,\;5,\;\tfrac{19}{4}\).

